textBeforeTable: Features and Specifications     BARD® FLUORO-4™ silicone ureteral stents have the insertion advantages found with urethane stents plus the biocompatibility of silicone stents. The silicone/tantalum formulation is highly radiopaque under imaging (radiology or fluoroscopy). It is packaged with a .038" lubricious coated guidewire for the 6 and 7 Fr. sizes and includes a push catheter and clamp. } } $(imageCountId).html(caption); var caption = (opts.currSlide + 1) + ' of ' + opts.slideCount; function onAfter(curr, next, opts) { }); } }); after: onAfter next: nextId, prev: prevId, startingSlide: 0, speed: 600, timeout: 8000, $(imageDivId).cycle({ if (imageCount > 1) { $(function () { var imageCount = 4; var imageCountId = '#pnlImageCount'; var nextId = '#pnlNext'; var prevId = '#pnlPrev'; var imageDivId = '#pnlImageSet'; {
